# Game dialog popups

Full guide: `blightsilver_game/context/GAME_DIALOG_POPUP_GUIDE.md`

## Required

For **player-facing** confirmations, alerts, choice menus, and text prompts, use the `GameDialog` autoload (`autoload/GameDialog.gd`):

- `GameDialog.confirmation_overlay()` — two buttons (confirm / Yes left, cancel right)
- `GameDialog.accept_overlay()` — single OK
- `GameDialog.choices_overlay()` — multiple actions
- `GameDialog.prompt_overlay()` — text input

Reuse styling helpers when needed: `make_panel_stylebox()`, `style_title_label()`, `style_body_label()`, `style_button()`.

Guard with `GameDialog.has_open_overlay(parent)` and close with `GameDialog.close_overlay(parent)` before scene changes when appropriate.

## Forbidden

- Godot native dialogs: `AcceptDialog`, `ConfirmationDialog`, `Window` popups for gameplay UI
- Hand-built modal UI with new `StyleBoxFlat` / unstyled `Button` per screen (like a one-off `PanelContainer` prompt)

## Allowed exceptions

- `FileDialog` / `EditorFileDialog` for import/export and admin file picking
- Editor-only tools (`VNEditor`, builders, vault managers)
- Dedicated full-screen overlays (VN, pack opening, battle overlays) — not generic confirm/alert boxes

## Examples in repo

- `DeckBuilder.gd` → `_confirm_high_cost_save()`
- `QuickDuel.gd` → `_show_tutorial_prompt()`

When adding a new popup type, extend `GameDialog.gd` once instead of styling a new popup in a feature script.
